stem in Nova Scotia, author Katherine Fierlbeck outlines the organizational and regulatory frameworks structuring provincial health care, while providing a detailed assessment of Nova Scotia’s health financing, physical infrastructure, service provision, and the efficacy of technological resources used in data tracking and health quality assessments. Structured for ease of comparison, Nova Scotia: A Health System Profile will, along with other volumes in the series, help scholars draw analytic evidence-based policy conclusions about the health system of Nova Scotia and other Canadian provinces and territories.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aMedical carezNova Scotia. 0aMedical policyzNova Scotia. 7aMEDICAL / Health Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060679940uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148751592840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487515928423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487515928.jpg  a978-3-11-060679-9  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles